choices.text: Given a set of squares representing a cross section of a tree, assign rings from the outer parts of the tree to the inner as follows: calling the non-tree grid squares ring $0$ , each ring $n$ is made up of all those grid squares that have at least one ring $(n-1)$ square as a neighbor (where neighboring squares are those that share an edge).
